It will also be a customer service nightmare. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usyrinxxayonaero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syrinxx AyonaeRo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/4/02 2:31:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2718.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.zianet.com/syrinxx/kick.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bazaar now on Test</span><hr size=1> Ok I just patched up for test and tried out the new Bazaar.  It really is good.  You zone in and type /bazaar to bring up a special window that allows you to search for sale items by a bunch of different filters, such as seller, item name, price, item slot, race, class, etc.  <br>
<br>
Or you can just wander around the bazaar and right click people's merchants to browse their goods like a normal merchant.  The traders have the same name as their owner (e.g. &quot;Syrinxx's Trader&quot;) and they even have the same race as their owner  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
For sellers, you just buy a Trader's satchel and bring up the /trader window to place your items in and set the prices.  Then you click on &quot;Start Trader&quot; and voila you have your own 10 slot merchant.<br>
<br>
I think this is going to drastically change how buying and selling works.  For one, buyers will be able to sort their search results by price, so I anticipate big price wars on common items like Kunark armor and Sebilis items.  When people see your Singing Steel Gauntlets listed at 400 and all the others are 500, you've got an easy sale.  I figure sellers will do a price check on their stuff using the /bazaar window before they set the price for their items.  This is good news for people seeking a bargain.<br>
<br>
On another note, the new interface ROCKS.  But that's something for another post  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukarmonshadowstalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karmon Shadowstalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/4/02 3:23:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2718.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bazaar now on Test</span><hr size=1> This'll definitely be good for buyers in search of low-medium value items, like Kunark armor. I don't think the higher end items (20k+) will be too affected, though, as you usually don't see many sellers with them. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105424>Beowuulf</a><BR><a href=http://www.steelwarrior.org>Warlord</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uakomofcazicthule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akom of Cazic Thule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/4/02 5:29:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2718.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://sanguinecrusaders.homestead.com/files/Akom_Jump.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bazaar now on Test</span><hr size=1> Instructions from the patch message, taken from Castersrealm:<br>
<br>
Let the Bazaar Testing begin! <br>
Vendors <br>
<br>
- First, create or purchase Trader Satchels from an NPC merchant in the bazaar. <br>
<br>
- Second, place tradable items in the bags. <br>
<br>
- At this time you can type /trader and begin setting prices on the items you wish to sell. <br>
<br>
- Once you have some prices set and you wish to open shop, you must go to a trading area. These are the rows of tents in the bazaar. <br>
<br>
- Click Begin Trader. At this time people will be able to buy from you. <br>
<br>
Buyers <br>
<br>
- To search the bazaar for items for sale, type /bazaar <br>
<br>
- To purchase from a player merchant, right click on them as if you were buying from an NPC vendor. <br>
<br>
Notes <br>
<br>
- The bazaar only works in the new user interface! For instructions on how to switch over to the new UI, please click here. <br>
<br>
- You can only be a trader in the trading stalls (rows of tents). <br>
<br>
- The name over your head will change slightly when in trading mode. <br>
<br>
- The prices that you set for items are stored in your EQ directory. The next time you attempt to sell the same item, the bazaar will assume that you want to use similar pricing until you say otherwise. <br>
<br>
- When you close up shop, anyone viewing your current stock will automatically end trading with you. <br>
<br>
- The EverQuest Development Team <br>
